The paper focuses on visual question answering (VQA) using natural language queries and images, which falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel method that involves reasoning and graph-based techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques to infer missing information. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.IR.
